of Containment." <date>1980</date> (2 copies)</p><p> 3. The Origins of the Union and of the States. Separate from the Proceedings of the Massachusettes Historical Society. Vol. 72, (<date>1957-1960</date>)</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_4774b37bb5d1ef6ebc48e6abaa0d5dbd" level="file"><did><unittitle>Twenty-six letters from Curtis Nettels to Van Wyck Brooks, the American author, critic, and translator</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1952/1954" type="inclusive">1952-1954</unitdate><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1958/1963" type="inclusive">1958-1963</unitdate><container id="aspace_50928b18b30d897ae62b32d6355fcb79" label="Mixed Materials [31924065182879]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_780758291cf3572390efbdbaadc2f3dc" parent="aspace_50928b18b30d897ae62b32d6355fcb79" type="folder">41</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_f553e296c5fc06ec844358196f5fb445"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>The letters deal mainly with American writers and American literature, some political issues and also discussion of Mr. Brook's books. Some examples of his well known books are: <title>The Wine of the Puritans</title>, <date>1909</date>; <title>America's Coming of Age</title>, <date>1915</date>; <title>The Ordeal of Mark Twain</title>, <date>1920</date>; <title>The Pilgrimage of Henry James</title>, <date>1925</date>; <title>The Life of Emerson</title>, <date>1932</date>; <title>The Flowering of New England</title>, <date>1936</date>; <title>New England: Indian Summer</title>, <date>1940</date>; <title>The World of Washington Irving</title>, <date>1944</date>; <title>The Confident Years</title>, <date>1952</date>; <title>The Writer in America</title>, <date>1953</date>; <title>Helen Keller, Sketch for a Portrait</title>, <date>1956</date>; <title>Days of the Phoenix</title>, 1957</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_fc8ec6aa31972b250d8cc115fcb6a994" level="file"><did><unittitle>Letters</unittitle><unitdate calenda